%20HVAC%20vents%20wouldn't%20attract%20renters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22brick%20house%20with%20a%20sign%20out%20front%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6894d973cfc04e97619b059b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECole's%20Baltimore%20home.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Ryan%20Cole%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20thought%20the%20remodel%20was%20a%20bad%20idea%2C%20and%20we%20should%20just%20sell.%20I%2C%20however%2C%20wanted%20a%20shot%20at%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsell-investment-property-stopped-being-landlord-put-money-in-market-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eproperty%20portfolio%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20we%20agreed%20to%20move%20forward.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20she%20was%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20of%20the%20renovation%20was%20initially%20supposed%20to%20be%20under%20%24100%2C000.%20By%20the%20end%2C%20it%20had%20more%20than%20doubled%2C%20to%20about%20%24200%2C000.%20It%20took%20nearly%20four%20times%20as%20long%20as%20we%20thought.%20Meanwhile%2C%20mortgage%20payments%20continued%20to%20chip%20away%20at%20our%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2216f4a8e0-4b13-45fa-a017-9d9c18dcdf95%5C%22%3EWe%20had%20to%20redo%20a%20lot%20of%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20began%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-renovations-that-increase-property-value-real-estate-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efirst%20round%20of%20remodeling%3C%2Fa%3E%20around%20the%20same%20time%20we%20moved%20out%2C%20which%20was%20at%20the%20start%20of%20COVID.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20first%20project%20manager%20paid%20out%20in%20full%20to%20subcontractors%2C%20but%20the%20work%20was%20lacking%2C%20and%20after%20about%20nine%20months%20and%20%2475%2C000%20in%20charges%2C%20all%20we'd%20really%20accomplished%20was%20the%20demo%20of%20the%20old%20walls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20COVID%20was%20in%20full%20swing%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-outlook-new-home-construction-builder-confidence-covid-low-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecosts%20soared%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20we%20lost%20our%20first%20general%20contractor%2C%20the%20new%20one%20had%20to%20fix%20the%20issues%20with%20the%20previous%20work.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20HVAC%20was%20installed%20wrong%20and%20all%20the%20ductwork%20had%20to%20be%20taken%20out%20and%20redone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20the%20framing%20of%20the%20walls%20for%20hanging%20drywall%20was%20so%20bad%20that%20it%20was%20hard%20to%20find%20a%20right%20angle.%20We%20had%20to%20trash%20it%20all%20and%20buy%20new%20lumber%20%E2%80%94%20at%20higher%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELumber%20in%20the%20US%20had%20gone%20from%20%24320%20per%20thousand%20board-feet%20in%20April%202020%2C%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS1389934121002719%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%241%2C500%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20year%20later%2C%20which%20just%20so%20happened%20to%20be%20when%20we%20were%20re-remodeling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22newly%20renovated%20kitchen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6894d888194a2d49b8ae2cf4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECole's%20newly-renovated%20kitchen%20in%20their%20Baltimore%20home.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Ryan%20Cole%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPrices%20for%20construction%20materials%20had%20also%20increased%20an%20average%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fblog%2F2021%2Fa-look-at-the-price-of-construction.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E20%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20compared%20to%20the%20year%20prior.%20Our%20countertops%20and%20cabinets%20alone%20were%20nearly%20%2425%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20price%