0but%20important%20part%20of%20the%20solution%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%201974%2C%20the%20federal%20government%20has%20regulated%20manufactured%20homes%20under%20a%20set%20of%20rules%20known%20as%20the%20HUD%20code%2C%20which%20overrides%20state%20and%20local%20building%20codes.%20The%20idea%20was%20to%20modernize%20and%20standardize%20trailers%20and%20mobile%20homes%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20permanent%20chassis%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20HUD%20code%2C%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.urban.org%2Furban-wire%2Fthree-reasons-we-still-build-its-1900%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edramatically%20shrunk%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20manufactured%20housing%20industry%20since%20the%201970s.%20There's%20evidence%20the%20chassis%20requirement%20was%20pushed%20by%20traditional%20homebuilders%20to%20suppress%20the%20booming%20manufactured%20housing%20industry%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Fpolicy%2F420254%2Fhousing-reform-congress-manufactured-homes-chassis-rule%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVox's%20Rachel%20Cohen%20recently%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Today%2C%20about%20100%2C000%20manufactured%20homes%20are%20produced%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20down%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huduser.gov%2Fpublications%2Fpdf%2Ffactory.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20peak%20of%20nearly%20580%2C000%20in%201973%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20make%20up%20less%20than%2010%25%20of%20all%20new%20construction%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20manufactured%20ADU%20built%20by%20Villa%20Homes%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689357503d5881a51c1eb0e9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmerican%20home-building%20productivity%20has%20stagnated.%20Some%20believe%20manufactured%20homes%20could%20help.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Villa%20Homes%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20we%20build%20cars%2C%20planes%2C%20and%20boats%20much%20more%20efficiently%20than%20ever%20before%2C%20American%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fdigest%2F202502%2Fstagnation-us-construction-productivity%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehome-building%20productivity%20has%20stagnated%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20in%20part%20because%20the%20industry%20still%20does%20so%20much%20on-site%2C%20custom%20construction%2C%20forgoing%20the%20benefits%20of%20standardization%2C%20climate%20control%2C%20and%20speed%20that%20factories%20offer.%20Pre-fabricated%20buildings%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0or%20parts%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0can%20be%20produced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jchs.harvard.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fresearch%2Ffiles%2Fharvard_jchs_pew_report_1_updated_0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20cheaply%20and%20efficiently%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20workers%20prepare%20the%20foundation%2C%20the%20home%20can%20simultaneously%20be%20constructed%20indoors%20without%20weather%20and%20other%20interruptions%20slowing%20down%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20bipartisan%20consensus%20around%20deregulating%20HUD-code%20housing%20has%20been%20building%20for%20years.%20In%20a%20major%20change%20to%20the%20regulations%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20last%20year%20reformed%20the%20code%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnlihc.org%2Fresource%2Fhud-announces-major-updates-manufactured-home-construction-and-safety-standards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallow%20up%20to%20four%20dwelling%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%20per%20manufactured%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it%20will%20take%20more%20than%20just%20federal%20deregulation%20to%20fully%20unleash%20the%20industry%20and%20disrupt%20traditional%20homebuilding.%20Manufactured%20housing%20faces%20other%20challenges%2C%20including%20a%20lack%20of%20consistent%20demand%20and%20investment%2C%20high%20costs%20of%20transporting%20a%20finished%20product%20to%20the%20building%20